parameters.content:
### 🖼️ Automated Product Data Extraction from Website Screenshots

This workflow starts when a new row is added in Google Sheets containing a product page URL. It triggers Dumpling AI to capture a screenshot of the site. The image is downloaded using an HTTP Request, then converted from binary to base64. Dumpling AI is called again to extract product information (like product name, price, discount, and ratings) directly from the screenshot. The Edit Fields node maps all the extracted details, and the final Google Sheets node updates your spreadsheet with the structured product data next to the original URL.

Use this workflow to save hours of manual copy-paste work, speed up cataloging, and ensure your product database is always fresh and accurate.
